getDAO

public static <T extends DAO> T getDAO(java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
                            throws DAONotFoundException
Returns DAO implementation by DAO class. Typical usage: 
 AccountDAO     dao     = DAOManager.getDAO(AccountDAO.class);

Type Parameters:
T - Subclass of DAO
Parameters:
clazz - Abstract DAO class implementation of which was registered
Returns:
DAO implementation
Throws:
DAONotFoundException - if DAO implementation not found

registerDAO

public static void registerDAO(java.lang.Class<? extends DAO> daoClass)
                        throws DAOAlreadyRegisteredException,
                               java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                               java.lang.InstantiationException
Registers DAO.
First it creates new instance of DAO, then invokes DAO.supports(String, int, int)
. If the result was possitive - it associates DAO instance with DAO.getClassName()
If another DAO was registed - DAOAlreadyRegisteredException will be thrown

Parameters:
daoClass - DAO implementation
Throws:
DAOAlreadyRegisteredException - if DAO is already registered
java.lang.IllegalAccessException - if something went wrong during instantiation of DAO
java.lang.InstantiationException - if something went wrong during instantiation of DAO

unregisterDAO

public static void unregisterDAO(java.lang.Class<? extends DAO> daoClass)
Unregisters DAO class

Parameters:
daoClass - DAO implementation to unregister
